# Rapid Cortex — Cursor Rules
# Real-Time AI Intelligence for Emergency Response
# Senior Full-Stack Engineer, AWS Architect, and UI/UX Design standards

## PROJECT OVERVIEW

Rapid Cortex is a production public safety intelligence platform for:
- 911 dispatch centers / PSAPs
- Emergency communications centers
- Law enforcement, fire, EMS
- Emergency management agencies
- Product verticals: Campus Safety, Venue Operations, Hospital Routing

It enhances operations but does NOT replace CAD, telephony, dispatchers, or medical direction.

**Role dashboard UI/UX (navigation, widgets, visual themes, "cannot" lists):** see `docs/role-dashboard-spec.md` — canonical spec for all 21 active roles. Implement absent UI for forbidden actions; never gray out permanent RBAC denials.

**Sidebar navigation (all 21 roles):** single source of truth in `apps/web/lib/navigation/role-nav.ts`. Resolve with `getRoleNav(role, buildNavContext(user, jurisdictionSlug))`, filter features via `filterRoleNavByFeatures`, render with `RoleNavSidebar` / `RoleNavSections`. VIEW ONLY label badges stay visible; feature-gated items omit when flag is off.

